{"pageProps":{"tutorial":{"title":"Ways to Add CSS","slug":"css-implementation","subject":"CSS","category":"Web Development","level":"Beginner","estimated_read_time":"12 mins","prerequisites":["CSS Syntax"],"learning_objectives":["Learn the three ways to insert CSS","Understand External CSS","Understand Internal CSS","Understand Inline CSS","Know when to use which method"],"theory":"There are three ways of inserting a style sheet:\n\n1.  **External CSS**: The styles are defined in a separate `.css` file and linked in the HTML `<head>`. This is the best practice for professional websites.\n2.  **Internal CSS**: The styles are defined within the `<style>` element, inside the `<head>` section of an HTML page. Good for single-page unique styles.\n3.  **Inline CSS**: The styles are defined strictly within the `style` attribute of a specific HTML element. This is generally discouraged as it mixes content with presentation.","syntax":"<!-- External -->\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"styles.css\">\n\n<!-- Internal -->\n<style>\n  body { background-color: linen; }\n</style>\n\n<!-- Inline -->\n<h1 style=\"color:blue;\">This is a Blue Heading</h1>","examples":[{"code":"<head>\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"mystyle.css\">\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>This is a heading</h1>\n</body>","output":"The heading styling depends on mystyle.css content.","explanation":"This demonstrates how to link an external stylesheet."}],"common_mistakes":[{"mistake":"Overusing Inline CSS","correction":"Avoid inline CSS. It makes maintenance difficult and overrides external styles.","example":"WRONG: <p style=\"color:red;\">Text</p> on every paragraph.\nCORRECT: p { color: red; } in a .css file."}],"interview_questions":[{"question":"Which CSS implementation method has the highest priority?","answer":"Inline CSS has the highest priority among the three (excluding !important). It overrides Internal and External styles.","difficulty":"Medium"},{"question":"What is the benefit of External CSS?","answer":"It allows you to change the look of an entire website by changing just one file. It also creates a clean separation of concerns.","difficulty":"Easy"}],"practice_problems":[{"problem":"Write the HTML code to link a file named 'theme.css'.","hint":"Use the <link> tag.","solution":"<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"theme.css\">","difficulty":"Easy"}],"real_world_use_cases":[{"scenario":"Site-wide Theme Updates","description":"When a company changes its brand color, updating one Variable in an external CSS file updates thousands of pages instantly.","code":":root { --primary-color: #newColor; }"}],"exam_notes":["Inline styles behave like they have higher specificity than internal or external styles.","External styles are linked using the <link> tag.","Internal styles are written inside <style> tags."],"summary":"While there are three ways to add CSS, External CSS is the industry standard for scalable, maintainable web applications.","order":40},"courseTutorials":[{"slug":"css-introduction","path":"content/css/css-introduction.json","title":"Introduction to CSS","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":1},{"slug":"css-syntax","path":"content/css/css-syntax.json","title":"CSS Syntax","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":2},{"slug":"css-best-practices","path":"content/css/css-best-practices.json","title":"CSS Best Practices","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":3},{"slug":"css-borders","path":"content/css/css-borders.json","title":"CSS Borders","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":4},{"slug":"css-colors","path":"content/css/css-colors.json","title":"CSS Colors","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":5},{"slug":"css-backgrounds","path":"content/css/css-backgrounds.json","title":"CSS Backgrounds","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":6},{"slug":"css-comments","path":"content/css/css-c